"The train is derailed, but there are no casualties among the passengers," said the local police, explaining how the only two surviving elephants were taken care of by the members of the reserve. The videos filmed after the accident, which had a strong echo on social media, show the extent of the impact, with animals lying, between blood pools, near the tracks..&nbsp;
Killing or wounding elephants is a criminal offence in Sri Lanka, which has about 7,000 wild elephants and where these huge mammals are considered a national treasure, partly because of their importance in Buddhist culture. For the authorities is &nbsp; the worst incident of this type recorded on the island. > In September 2018, in fact, two elephant puppies and their pregnant mother were killed in the same region in a similar collusion that involved, even in that case, a convoy in march.&nbsp; Since then, authorities have ordered train drivers to comply with speed limits to avoid hurting elephants when they are in areas where they are likely to cross the tracks.
