It is an easy time for the coexistence between elephants and men in Sri Lanka. Today's incident arrives a few days after the words of concern expressed by the government for the increasing number of clashes in some regions of the island. The peasants, desperate for the continuous looting and destruction of their crops, which often represent the only means of sustenance, &nbsp; they increasingly attack me. As stated on Sunday by Anton Jayakody, Deputy Minister of the Environment, in this feud 450 elephants and 150 people were killed only in 2023. The Minister said that the new government intends to end this problem by preventing elephants from crossing villages. "We plan to introduce several barriers - which could include electrical fences, trenches or other deterrents - to make it more difficult for wild elephants to venture into villages," Jayakod concluded.
