Weidel, although she is married to a woman, with whom she grows two children, is then among the most daunting fairs of any policy of extension of the rights of Lgbt people. In line with this idea, at the last congress he promised that if he went to the government he will close all courses of "gender studies" in German universities. Finally, from the economic point of view, AfD's leader professed liberalism, focusing on a large cut of taxes and a 'super-sburocratization'.&nbsp;
