Despite record improperity, the 66-year leader of the Social-Democrats - the oldest party in the country that today faces a serious crisis of consensus - is firmly convinced that its combination and its composure will allow it to secure a new mandate to lead the &nbsp;Germany, as it happened against every forecast at the previous elections. To the government since 2021 - after being Minister of Finance and Vice Chancellor of Merkel since 2018 - Olaf Scholz has managed to gather the necessary confidence to lead the "semaforo" coalition, shipwrecked in November following the release of the Fdp liberals from the executive. In its 4 years at the Bundeskanzleramt has increased unemployment benefits through the Burgergeld - a social benefit aimed at people who are skilled at work, who are in disrespect - introduced the minimum pension 'Grundrente' and, on thrust from Green, the Climate and Transformation Fund (Ktf) from 212 billion.
Its recipe to try to regain land is a left-hand shift through a campaign in which the Social Democrats defend the rise of the minimum wage, the reduction of VAT on food at 5% and better protection for tenants. From the end of January, Olaf Scholz has strongly mobilized against his conservative rival Friedrich Merz, criticized for allying with the far-right party AfD in order to carry out the immigration law. He also accused his opponent and probable new chancellor, of being a "hot head". This is why he is nominated as a 'reassurance' of a&nbsp;Germany&nbsp; he is increasingly disoriented by the economic crisis and geopolitical upheaval. &nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2>SAHRA WAGENKNECHT, THE FUTURE OF THE SYSTEM
Historical member of the German left and supporter of an even more radical line than that of the parties in which he miliated, Sahra Wagenknecht, 55 years - after breaking with the Linke - in January 2024 he founded the alliance that bears his name (Bsw) and with which he nominates the stationary, with the doubt if he can access the Lower House of the German Parliament. Known for his closest ideas to conservative formations - such as the refusal of immigration - despite his great success in the first three regional elections in Saxony, Thuringia and Brandenburg, where his party emerged as a third force with 11.8% respectively, 15.8% and 13.5% of the votes, according to the last polls his entry to the Bundestag is at risk.
Equipped with a strong charism that has earned her respect for many of her political opponents, her party combines the typical demands of the left - such as measures to combat social inequality - with proposals closer to the right, such as the limitation of immigration to give priority to German workers or the defense of jobs in industry regarding environmental concerns. This mix of positions, which made it popular among the supporters of the extreme right of AfD, earned it the nickname "red-brown". Its proposal on immigration is the imposition of a maximum threshold of 50,000 foreigners a year between migrants and refugees. The Russian-Ukrainian conflict believes "both the parties" responsible for the outbreak of war.&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2>CHRISTIAN LINDNER, THE FREEDOM AMMIRA MILEI> </h2>
The president of the German Liberal Party (Fdp), Christian Lindner, 46 years old - who recently confessed to his admiration for Argentine President Javier Milei and the magnate Elon Musk - is at the most critical moment of a political career that has been lightning and that now could reach a sudden end. "We must have the courage to have more Milei and more Musk," Lindner said shortly after he came out of the coalition he was part of as Finance Minister. The statement on Musk and Milei indicated two essential elements of the Fdp, which are the demand for reduction of bureaucracy and greater entrepreneurial freedom.
